Here’s a precise confirmation of what’s in the file and how it maps to your app needs.</p>
<hr data-start="157" data-end="160">
<h2 data-section-id="qd4m5d" data-start="162" data-end="199">What the file contains (confirmed)</h2>
<p data-start="201" data-end="331">The PDF is a <strong data-start="214" data-end="244">set of official scorecards</strong>, organised by <strong data-start="259" data-end="269">course</strong> and <strong data-start="274" data-end="281">tee</strong>, with <strong data-start="288" data-end="330">hole-by-hole Par and Stroke Index (SI)</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="333" data-end="415">Across pages 1–4, the pattern is consistent <span class="relative inline-flex items-center select-none" type="button" aria-haspopup="dialog" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="radix-_r_e2_" data-state="closed"><button type="button" class="ms-1 relative flex h-[25px] select-none items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded-xl px-2 text-[10px] leading-[13px] corner-superellipse/1.1 text-token-text-secondary! hover:text-token-text-primary! hover:bg-token-bg-secondary dark:bg-token-main-surface-secondary dark:hover:bg-token-bg-secondary bg-[#f4f4f4] "><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="h-[16px] w-[16px] object-contain text-token-text-primary! flex-none icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fec7759e.svg#554074" fill="currentColor"></use></svg><p class="not-prose mt-0! mb-0! flex-auto truncate">NZ Golf Tour - Scorecards (unch…</p></button></span>:</p>
<h3 data-section-id="1bebd8s" data-start="417" data-end="448">Per course + tee, you have:</h3>
<ul data-start="449" data-end="613">
<li data-section-id="1hgnzo4" data-start="449" data-end="474">
<p data-start="451" data-end="474"><strong data-start="451" data-end="466">Hole number</strong>: 1–18</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="bjxgi9" data-start="475" data-end="550">
<p data-start="477" data-end="550"><strong data-start="477" data-end="487">Meters</strong>: distance (not required for your app unless you want it later)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1scyzn" data-start="551" data-end="575">
<p data-start="553" data-end="575"><strong data-start="553" data-end="560">Par</strong>: integer (3–5)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="184gepa" data-start="576" data-end="613">
<p data-start="578" data-end="613"><strong data-start="578" data-end="599">SI (Stroke Index)</strong>: integer 1–18</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="lwhiba" data-start="615" data-end="651">Courses identified (NZ Tour set)</h3>
<p data-start="652" data-end="694">Examples visible across the pages include:</p>
<ul data-start="695" data-end="973">
<li data-section-id="1ocdl9v" data-start="695" data-end="728">
<p data-start="697" data-end="728">Te Arai – <strong data-start="707" data-end="716">North</strong> (Back Tees)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1s1bynd" data-start="729" data-end="762">
<p data-start="731" data-end="762">Te Arai – <strong data-start="741" data-end="750">South</strong> (Back Tees)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="3iio77" data-start="763" data-end="786">
<p data-start="765" data-end="786">Titirangi (Blue Tees)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1901yzg" data-start="787" data-end="824">
<p data-start="789" data-end="824">Royal Auckland &amp; Grange (Blue Tees)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="177w41q" data-start="825" data-end="832">
<p data-start="827" data-end="832">Tieke</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ijr1m4" data-start="833" data-end="842">
<p data-start="835" data-end="842">Kinloch</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1egww1v" data-start="843" data-end="853">
<p data-start="845" data-end="853">Wairakei</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1vigknm" data-start="854" data-end="871">
<p data-start="856" data-end="871">Cape Kidnappers</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="9904x4" data-start="872" data-end="891">
<p data-start="874" data-end="891">Paraparaumu Beach</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="c83op2" data-start="892" data-end="910">
<p data-start="894" data-end="910">Royal Wellington</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="17kp4fr" data-start="911" data-end="922">
<p data-start="913" data-end="922">Millbrook</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1h5qnsj" data-start="923" data-end="936">
<p data-start="925" data-end="936">Remarkables</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="hw710t" data-start="937" data-end="951">
<p data-start="939" data-end="951">Jack’s Point</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1figjlf" data-start="952" data-end="963">
<p data-start="954" data-end="963">Arrowtown</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="68w0zq" data-start="964" data-end="973">
<p data-start="966" data-end="973">Coronet</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="975" data-end="1022">Each course/tee block is internally consistent:</p>
<ul data-start="1023" data-end="1172">
<li data-section-id="1e9d6f6" data-start="1023" data-end="1045">
<p data-start="1025" data-end="1045">Exactly <strong data-start="1033" data-end="1045">18 holes</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="e5bfnk" data-start="1046" data-end="1096">
<p data-start="1048" data-end="1096">SI values are a <strong data-start="1064" data-end="1096">complete permutation of 1–18</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1m4nwpf" data-start="1097" data-end="1172">
<p data-start="1099" data-end="1172">OUT / IN / TOTAL rows are summary only (we will ignore these for loading)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1174" data-end="1177">
<h2 data-section-id="157mktf" data-start="1179" data-end="1220">How this maps cleanly to your database</h2>
<p data-start="1222" data-end="1303">This file is already in the <strong data-start="1250" data-end="1272">ideal logical form</strong> for loading into a table like:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1305" data-end="1380"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="contents"><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-(--code-block-surface) corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl [--code-block-surface:var(--bg-elevated-secondary)] dark:[--code-block-surface:var(--composer-surface-primary)] lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fec7759e.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼs ͼ16"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>course_holes
-----------
course_id
hole_number
tee
par
stroke_index</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1382" data-end="1393">Key points:</p>
<ul data-start="1395" data-end="1532">
<li data-section-id="1d50ksx" data-start="1395" data-end="1419">
<p data-start="1397" data-end="1419"><strong data-start="1397" data-end="1419">One row = one hole</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="12rrstn" data-start="1420" data-end="1471">
<p data-start="1422" data-end="1471"><strong data-start="1422" data-end="1441">Tee is explicit</strong> (Back / Blue / White / Black)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1887snx" data-start="1472" data-end="1504">
<p data-start="1474" data-end="1504">No derived or ambiguous values</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ctddm6" data-start="1505" data-end="1532">
<p data-start="1507" data-end="1532">No conflicts across holes</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1534" data-end="1563">Meters can be ignored safely.</p>
<hr data-start="1565" data-end="1568">
<h2 data-section-id="n9487t" data-start="1570" data-end="1616">One important decision we need (before SQL)</h2>
<p data-start="1618" data-end="1686">We need to align <strong data-start="1635" data-end="1659">tee names in the PDF</strong> with your app’s tee model:</p>
<p data-start="1688" data-end="1712">Your app currently uses:</p>
<ul data-start="1713" data-end="1760">
<li data-section-id="10okkg5" data-start="1713" data-end="1760">
<p data-start="1715" data-end="1760"><code data-start="1715" data-end="1732">tee = 'M' | 'F'</code> (from earlier scoring code)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1762" data-end="1780">But the file uses:</p>
<ul data-start="1781" data-end="1838">
<li data-section-id="naze90" data-start="1781" data-end="1794">
<p data-start="1783" data-end="1794"><code data-start="1783" data-end="1794">Back Tees</code></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="16xrxbl" data-start="1795" data-end="1808">
<p data-start="1797" data-end="1808"><code data-start="1797" data-end="1808">Blue Tees</code></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="i4t4vc" data-start="1809" data-end="1823">
<p data-start="1811" data-end="1823"><code data-start="1811" data-end="1823">White Tees</code></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="q4zuo8" data-start="1824" data-end="1838">
<p data-start="1826" data-end="1838"><code data-start="1826" data-end="1838">Black Tees</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="1h441mw" data-start="1840" data-end="1888">We need to agree on ONE of these approaches:</h3>
<p data-start="1890" data-end="1926"><strong data-start="1890" data-end="1926">Option A (most common, simplest)</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1927" data-end="2021">
<li data-section-id="3an5jc" data-start="1927" data-end="1960">
<p data-start="1929" data-end="1960">Treat <em data-start="1935" data-end="1958">all these tees as <code data-start="1954" data-end="1957">M</code></em></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ehnjik" data-start="1961" data-end="2021">
<p data-start="1963" data-end="2021">Choose the <em data-start="1974" data-end="1998">primary tee per course</em> (usually Back or Blue)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2023" data-end="2065"><strong data-start="2023" data-end="2065">Option B (more flexible, future-proof)</strong></p>
<ul data-start="2066" data-end="2141">
<li data-section-id="1nchiju" data-start="2066" data-end="2141">
<p data-start="2068" data-end="2072">Map:</p>
<ul data-start="2075" data-end="2141">
<li data-section-id="egqzj9" data-start="2075" data-end="2102">
<p data-start="2077" data-end="2102">Back / Black / Blue → <code data-start="2099" data-end="2102">M</code></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1cczy81" data-start="2105" data-end="2141">
<p data-start="2107" data-end="2141">(Ignore White unless needed later)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2143" data-end="2196"><strong data-start="2143" data-end="2196">Option C (schema extension – not recommended yet)</strong></p>
<ul data-start="2197" data-end="2244">
<li data-section-id="12rtbjw" data-start="2197" data-end="2244">
<p data-start="2199" data-end="2244">Add a <code data-start="2205" data-end="2215">tee_name</code> column and keep exact labels</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2246" data-end="2373">My recommendation for now: <strong data-start="2273" data-end="2290">Option A or B</strong>, depending on whether different courses in the tour genuinely play different tees.</p>
<hr data-start="2375" data-end="2378">
<h2 data-section-id="17jtwxw" data-start="2380" data-end="2434">What I want from you before writing SQL (next step)</h2>
<p data-start="2436" data-end="2451">Please confirm:</p>
<ol data-start="2453" data-end="2803">
<li data-section-id="1cmp5hx" data-start="2453" data-end="2567">
<p data-start="2456" data-end="2504"><strong data-start="2456" data-end="2502">Which tee should be loaded for each course</strong></p>
<ul data-start="2508" data-end="2567">
<li data-section-id="1pydsvd" data-start="2508" data-end="2567">
<p data-start="2510" data-end="2567">e.g. “Use Back Tees where available, otherwise Blue Tees”</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1l21rq6" data-start="2568" data-end="2678">
<p data-start="2571" data-end="2628"><strong data-start="2571" data-end="2591">Exact table name</strong> you currently use for hole pars/SI</p>
<ul data-start="2632" data-end="2678">
<li data-section-id="70pkk6" data-start="2632" data-end="2678">
<p data-start="2634" data-end="2678">(e.g. <code data-start="2640" data-end="2654">course_holes</code>, <code data-start="2656" data-end="2662">pars</code>, <code data-start="2664" data-end="2677">course_pars</code>)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1pnz1x7" data-start="2679" data-end="2803">
<p data-start="2682" data-end="2690">Whether:</p>
<ul data-start="2694" data-end="2803">
<li data-section-id="copumb" data-start="2694" data-end="2748">
<p data-start="2696" data-end="2748">You want <strong data-start="2705" data-end="2720">INSERT only</strong> (table currently empty), or</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1lqd9zf" data-start="2752" data-end="2803">
<p data-start="2754" data-end="2803"><strong data-start="2754" data-end="2764">UPSERT</strong> (safe re-run, overwrite existing rows)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="2805" data-end="2855">Once you confirm those, the <strong data-start="2833" data-end="2846">next step</strong> will be:</p>
<blockquote data-start="2857" data-end="2970">
<p data-start="2859" data-end="2970">Generate <strong data-start="2868" data-end="2899">explicit, safe SQL (UPSERT)</strong> for <em data-start="2904" data-end="2930">all NZ Tour 2026 courses</em>, ready to paste directly into Supabase.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="2972" data-end="2975">
<h3 data-section-id="1y075wz" data-start="2977" data-end="3040">Improved version of your question (as requested previously)</h3>
<p data-start="3041" data-end="3243">“Can you validate that this scorecard file cleanly supports loading hole-by-hole Par and Stroke Index data into my Supabase schema, and confirm how it maps to my course/tee model before generating SQL?”</p>
<p data-start="3245" data-end="3325">If you want me to proceed using that framing, just say <strong data-start="3300" data-end="3324">Use improved version</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="3327" data-end="3438" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">👉 Over to you: confirm <strong data-start="3351" data-end="3386">tee mapping choice + table name</strong>, and we’ll move to SQL generation (next step only).</p></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"><div aria-label="Response actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none touch:w-[calc(100%+--spacing(3.5))] -mt-1 w-[calc(100%+--spacing(2.5))] duration-[1.5s] focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto pointer-events-none [mask-image:linear-gradient(to_right,black_33%,transparent_66%)] [mask-size:300%_100%] [mask-position:100%_0%] motion-safe:transition-[mask-position] group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:[mask-position:0_0] has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:[mask-position:0_0]" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy response" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fec7759e.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button type="button" class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-surface-hover rounded-lg" aria-label="Good response" aria-pressed="false" data-testid="good-response-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fec7759e.svg#51753c" fi