<p data-start="40" data-end="117">Below is <strong data-start="49" data-end="74">full replacement code</strong> for <code data-start="79" data-end="111">app/m/tours/[id]/more/page.tsx</code> that:</p>
<ul data-start="119" data-end="698">
<li data-section-id="cv388u" data-start="119" data-end="205">
<p data-start="121" data-end="205">Keeps your <strong data-start="132" data-end="143">top row</strong> exactly the same (Tour details / Rehandicapping / Tour Admin)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="xxf6lz" data-start="206" data-end="342">
<p data-start="208" data-end="269">Adds a <strong data-start="215" data-end="268">new second row of 3 buttons above the PDF buttons</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start="272" data-end="342">
<li data-section-id="1dvbbwx" data-start="272" data-end="300">
<p data-start="274" data-end="300"><strong data-start="274" data-end="292">App User Guide</strong> (works)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1fz1y33" data-start="303" data-end="342">
<p data-start="305" data-end="342"><strong data-start="305" data-end="331">two blank placeholders</strong> (disabled)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-section-id="z9y476" data-start="343" data-end="406">
<p data-start="345" data-end="406">Keeps your <strong data-start="356" data-end="369">Tour PDFs</strong> section and signed-url open behavior</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="tpsduw" data-start="407" data-end="450">
<p data-start="409" data-end="450">Uses the correct bucket: <strong data-start="434" data-end="450"><code data-start="436" data-end="448">tours-pdfs</code></strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="v3x339" data-start="451" data-end="698">
<p data-start="453" data-end="698">Includes a small safety fix so if any DB <code data-start="494" data-end="508">storage_path</code> accidentally starts with <code data-start="534" data-end="542">tours/</code> while the object is actually stored under <code data-start="585" data-end="602">tours/tours/...</code>, it will auto-correct (this prevents “object not found” coming back again from a path mismatch)</p>
</li>
</ul>
